Agriculture stakeholders should partner with varsities to improve farming methods, University of Eldoret chancellor Judith Bahemuka has said.Speaking when she closed a three-day agribusiness trade fair at the university on Saturday, she said, We have contributed to the growth of the agriculture sector through research and training of agricultural professionals. Bahemuka urged stakeholders not to work in isolation. This will only make the situation worse, she said.Exhibitors included farm input suppliers, seed, fertiliser, fish farming and crop machinery companies.The theme of this year s fair was Towards Food Security and National Growth through Agricultural Innovation and Technology Transfer. 